# Sales Forecasting

A simple machine learning project to predict future sales based on historical sales data.

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to build a sales forecasting model using Python and machine learning techniques. The model analyzes historical sales data and predicts future sales to support better business decisions.

## 🚀 Features

- Data preprocessing and cleaning
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Feature engineering
- Model training and evaluation
- Sales prediction
- Data visualization

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn
- Jupyter Notebook

## 📂 Project Structure

```
Sales-Forecasting/
│── data/
│── notebooks/
│── models/
│── README.md
│── requirements.txt
│── sales_forecasting.ipynb
```

## ⚙️ Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/Sales-Forecasting.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project folder:
   ```bash
   cd Sales-Forecasting
   ```

3. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

## ▶️ Usage

Run the Jupyter Notebook:

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

Open `sales_forecasting.ipynb` and execute the cells.

## 📊 Results

The model predicts future sales based on historical trends. Performance can be evaluated using metrics such as:

- Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
- Mean Squared Error (MSE)
- R² Score

